-- Burundi’s Coffee Sales Increased 21% in January, Authority Says
-- B y   D e s i r e   N i m u b o n a
-- 2012-02-21T11:00:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-21/burundi-s-coffee-sales-increased-21-in-january-authority-says.html
Burundi sold 663,000 kilograms (1.46
million pounds) of coffee in January, 21 percent more than a
month earlier, according to the industry’s regulator.  Farmers in the East African nation earned $2.4 million from
the sales, up from $2.2 million in December, the Burundi Coffee
Authority said in a statement handed to reporters today in the
capital, Bujumbura.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Desire Nimubona in Bujumbura via Nairobi at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at   pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  